Authorities in Stockton, California continue to search for the suspect in Saturday's deadly mass shooting at a birthday party. The San Joaquin Sheriff says authorities have found a pair of weapons collected from the roof of the scene, but adds it's unclear yet if the guns are related to the shooting. NBC News' Steve Patterson has more details. A monster winter storm is moving east and could bring dangerous conditions to millions of people this week. The latest blast collided with Thanksgiving travel, sending planes sliding across tarmacs and cancelling thousands of flights. NBC News' Maggie Vespa reports.The Prometheus statue that sits right next to the iconic skating rink at Rockefeller Center was recently regilded with sheets of gold leaf by trained artisans. It's a facelift that happens every 25 years. NBC News' Joe Fryer reports.

videos.title: Dec 2 Tue
videos.overview: Across parts of the Northeast and New England, 14 million people remain under Winter alerts. A fast-moving storm wreaked havoc on roads and dumped up to 10 inches of snow in some areas. An arctic blast this week could bring record low temperatures to cities like Chicago and Detroit. NBC News' Erin McLaughlin reports. Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth said that he did not see the second strike on an alleged drug boat aimed at survivors of the initial U.S. attack. President Trump said the strikes are keeping drugs from reaching the American people. NBC News' Gabe Gutierrez reports.Russian President Vladimir Putin issued a new warning to European countries over Ukraine peace talks. The Kremlin also called Putin's meeting with Trump envoys productive'. NBC News' Keir Simmons reports. New images were released by prosecutors show the suspect in the ambush of two National Guard soldiers. Meanwhile the man accused in the shooting appeared in a virtual court hearing today, pleading not guilty to first degree murder and other charges. NBC News' Ryan Nobles reports. New video is raising fresh questions about the ability of driverless cars to navigate complicated scenes. NBC News' Liz Kreutz reports. Michael and Susan Dell appeared with President Trump at the White House to announce their gift that will help establish 25 million investment accounts for American children. NBC News' Christine Romans reports.The St. Johns County sheriff's office arrested three teenagers after they kicked in a stranger's front door, as part of the viral "door kick challenge". Similar incidents have been caught on camera across the country, and police warn the stunts are dangerous. NBC News' Emilie Ikeda reports.

videos.title: Dec 3 Wed
videos.overview: President Trump said he would have no problem' releasing any video of the second strike on an alleged drug boat in September that has come under scrutiny. NBC News' Gabe Gutierrez reports.A senior law enforcement official told NBC News that ICE is launching immigration enforcement operations in Minneapolis. It comes as President Trump is facing backlash in the city's Somali community over his recent comments. NBC News' Maggie Vespa reports. In Delaware, officers patrolling the area initiated a traffic stop and confronted a student in a park after hours. The man was armed with a loaded handgun, ammunition and an armored ballistic plate. NBC News' Sam Brock has the latest. Democrats on the House Oversight Committee released new photos and videos showing the inside of Jeffrey Epstein's home in the U.S. Virgin Islands. One image shows a room furnished with a dentist's chair and masks. NBC News' Ryan Nobles reports. A judge sentenced former doctor Salvador Plasencia to 30 months in prison for illegally selling ketamine to "Friends" star Matthew Perry. Plasencia apologized to Perry's family in court, admitting he failed the actor. NBC News' Camila Bernal reports. This year's Rockefeller Center Christmas Tree traveled to the heart of midtown from upstate New York. It was donated by a mother and her young son. They say this year's lighting will be an emotional tribute to someone they loved. NBC News' Joe Fryer reports.

videos.title: Dec 4 Thur
videos.overview: Admiral Frank Bradley briefed lawmakers behind closed doors over his decision to strike survivors of an initial U.S. attack on an alleged drug boat. There was divided reaction among Democrats and Republicans. NBC News' Courtney Kube reports.Prosecutors released the 911 call made by a McDonald's employee alerting police customers spotted a man who looked like the suspect in the murder of the UnitedHealthcare CEO. They also released never-before-seen photos of what Mangione was carrying, including thousands of dollars in cash. NBC News' Stephanie Gosk reports. The FBI arrested Brian Cole, Jr. and charged him in connection to pipe bombs placed outside the Democratic and Republican party headquarters in January 2021. NBC News' Kelly O'Donnell reports. In Virginia, first responders rushed to rescue two workers who were trapped 150 feet in the air after their window washing platform collapsed. NBC News' Ryan Nobles reports on the dramatic race to save them. NBC News obtained video showing the school bus engulfed by an inferno. A quick acting bus driver made sure all children were evacuated to safety. NBC News' George Solis reports. In our series "The Cost of Denial," NBC News' Kate Snow reports on the surgical procedure doctors say can help a 12-year-old competitive dancer struggling with scoliosis that insurance has denied. The girl's mother is trying everything she can to get coverage.

videos.title: Dec 5 Fri
videos.overview: When floodwaters started to rapidly rise early on July 4th, just two 911 operators were working. Hundreds of people called in, making desperate pleas for help. A warning: many of the calls are disturbing. NBC News' Ryan Chandler reports. A dangerous winter storm brought record low temperatures and icy road conditions. NBC News' Emilie Ikeda reports. As packages left outside home for delivery are targeted for theft this holiday season, police warn more thieves are using jammers to scramble the video on wifi connected home security cameras. NBC News' Adrienne Broaddus reports. A CDC panel of vaccine advisors voted to end a longstanding recommendation that all newborns get the hepatitis B vaccine at birth. Dr. Susan Kressly, the president of the American Academy of Pediatrics says because of the move, "children in America are less safe." NBC News' Anne Thompson reports. In a deal worth nearly $83 billion, Netflix says it will acquire key assets like Warner Bros. Studio and HBO after linear cable channels are spun off into a separate company. Top Hollywood associations like the Writers Guild are raising antitrust concerns as there are likely to be regulatory hurdles to the deal going through. NBC News' Chloe Melas reports.

videos.title: Dec 6 Sat
videos.overview: Around 20 million people across the West and Midwest are under winter alerts Saturday as a fast-moving storm delivers heavy snow, strong winds and blasts of cold that is blanketing cities like Chicago. NBC News' Adrienne Broaddus reports. Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth vowed more U.S. boat strikes in the Caribbean while speaking at a defense forum on Saturday. It comes as the Pentagon has faced growing scrutiny about those strikes on Capitol Hill. NBC News' Julie Tsirkin reports. Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said Russian drone strikes burned down a railway station in central Ukraine and hit residential and commercial buildings near Kyiv, killing at least one person. It comes as talks between the U.S. and Ukraine to try to end the war enter their third day. NBC News' Daniele Hamamdjian reports. Newly released cockpit audio and dashcam video obtained by NBC station KGW in Portland is shedding light on what happened during an in-flight emergency, when a former pilot tried to shut down the engines of a commercial plane. NBC News' Morgan Chesky reports. Netflix emailed its subscribers on Saturday in an effort to calm customers' concerns after the streaming giant announced a blockbuster deal to acquire Warner Bros. and HBO Max. NBC News' Chloe Melas reports. After an outpouring of donations, 88-year-old Ed Bambas was surprised with a life-changing check that will help him retire. NBC Nightly News anchor Tom Llamas reports. As 7-year-old Sutton Bullard battles cancer, Washington Capitals goalie Logan Thompson has become her biggest fan, cheering her on throughout her treatment journey and celebrating her victory once her treatment was complete. NBC News' Jos Daz-Balart has that story and more in this week's Good News Wrap-Up.

videos.title: Dec 7 Sun
videos.overview: Heavy snow continues to impact a large swath of the U.S. from the Midwest to the Northeast, causing flight cancellations and delays at airports across the country. NBC News' Adrienne Broaddus reports. Prosecutors released new evidence photos in their case against Luigi Mangione, the suspect accused of killing UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson. It comes ahead of a critical hearing that could determine what evidence will be allowed in his trial. NBC News' Valerie Castro reports. U.S. and Ukrainian officials indicated over the weekend that peace talks to end the war with Russia are making progress, even as Russia bombards Ukraine with a series of deadly strikes. NBC News' Keir Simmons reports. President Trump signaled plans to escalate his administration's military campaign in the Caribbean, as Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth said that U.S. strikes on alleged drug boats will continue. NBC News' Gabe Gutierrez reports. The 2025 holiday shopping season is already breaking records, but consumers are pulling back their spending at the same time, highlighting a greater divide in who's spending record amounts of money this year. NBC News' Vicky Nguyen has more. One Louvre official telling French media Sunday that a water leak damaged hundreds of items in the Egyptian antiquities department, just weeks after a high-profile jewel heist raised concerns about the museum's security. NBC News' Daniele Hamamdjian reports. Residents in Altadena, California, are moving forward after the Eaton Fire devastated the region earlier this year, with the community bringing back its time-honored holiday tradition, "Christmas Tree Lane," for the holiday season. NBC News' Hallie Jackson has the story.

videos.title: Dec 8 Mon
videos.overview: As arctic air blasts across the mid-Atlantic, a series of storms are dumping rain and snow. The dangerous conditions left schools in Virginia closed today as parts of the state got up to five inches of snow. Chicago has been slammed with 17 inches of snow so far and is expected to be impacted by another system that's on the move. NBC News' Adrienne Broaddus reports. A powerful 7.6-magnitude earthquake hit off the coast of Japan, sparking fires and triggering a tsunami warning. NBC News' Janis Mackey Frayer reports. Luigi Mangione was back in court for a pretrial hearing over evidence. The officer who first searched his backpack revealed she found a wet pair of underwear wrapped around a loaded magazine. Prosecutors have also released photos of the clothing Mangione was wearing and a necklace with a USB drive. NBC News' Stephanie Gosk reports. A father and son got stranded in a remote Florida swamp after their ATV ran out of gas. The pair called 911, and the sheriff's department was able to find them and pull off a dramatic helicopter rescue. NBC News' George Solis reports. A family says they believe a deceased loved one's home in California was targeted by burglars two days after they posted her obituary in a local newspaper. Authorities in Michigan and New York have also arrested thieves for using the tactic. NBC News' Liz Kreutz reports. Newly released video and audio recordings reveal the terrifying moments in 2023 when an off-duty pilot attempted to shut down the engines of an airliner. NBC News' Tom Costello has the story. President Trump announced $12 billion in aid for farmers impacted by the trade war with China. NBC News' Garrett Haake reports. After Netflix announced a deal to buy Warner Bros. Studios, HBO, and HBO Max, David Ellison's Paramount went directly to shareholders with a bid to buy the entirety of Warner Bros. Discovery. President Trump has indicated he will be involved in reviewing the offers to see if a deal should be allowed to go through. NBC News' Chloe Melas reports.On the Friday before final exams, students at Taylor University in Indiana dress up in costumes and pack into the stands to watch the men's basketball team. Unlike other games, they watch in complete silence until the home team's tenth point is scored, a tradition that started more than 25 years ago. NBC Nightly News anchor Tom Llamas reports.

videos.title: Dec 9 Tue
videos.overview: Officials said a suspect was in custody after a shooting at Kentucky State University. One person was killed and another injured according to police. NBC News' Emilie Ikeda reports. Body camera video shows police coming face-to-face with Luigi Mangione in a McDonald's in Pennsylvania. Mangione had been on the run for five days. The video shows Mangione handing police a fake ID from New Jersey. NBC News' Stephanie Gosk reports. The average homeowner can expect heating costs to go up 7.6% this winter as natural gas and electricity prices drive the increase. NBC News' Tom Costello reports.President Trump will tout progress lowering prices in a Pennsylvania speech, while many voters there say they are frustrated by the cost of living. NBC News' Garrett Haake reports. A man was hiking in Arches National Park in Utah when he became trapped in quicksand. Rescuers used shovels and ladders to help him pull himself to safety. Quicksand incidents are rare, but can be dangerous. NBC News' Morgan Chesky reports. A small plane had to make an emergency landing on a highway in Florida. It collided with a Toyota Camry, with a 57-year-old woman inside. Miraculously, the woman suffered only minor injuries, according to fire rescue. The two men on board were not injured. NBC News' George Solis reports. Millions are under flood watches as days of heavy rain are expectedto soak parts of the Pacific Northwest. Meanwhile, two clipper systems are on the way bringing more snow and strong winds. NBC News' Erin McLaughlin reports from Poughkeepsie, New York.

videos.title: Dec 10 Wed
videos.overview: President Trump announced the U.S. seized an oil tanker off the Venezuelan coast. Video showed an elite coast guard team boarding the vessel, executing what Attorney General Pam Bondi said was a "seizure warrant" issued by a judge. NBC News' Garrett Haake reports. ICE officers made new arrests as part of an ongoing law enforcement operation in Minneapolis. NBC News' Gabe Gutierrez reports. Across the country, there have been more than 1,900 measles cases this year, according to new numbers released by the CDC. Meanwhile in South Carolina, health officials report more than two dozen new cases across the state since Friday. NBC News' Emilie Ikeda has the story. In North Carolina, more than half of insurance denials that go through external review in the state's Smart NC program are overturned. NBC News' Vicky Nguyen reports on one family that used the system to get approval for the medicine that is helping cut down on their son's seizures - the list price nearly $800,000 a year. A pregnant woman gave birth inside a Waymo taxi as the car drove her to the hospital, the company said. NBC News' Liz Kreutz reports.

videos.title: Dec 11 Thur
videos.overview: The Senate failed to pass two different health care plans, which means premiums will spike for many people who rely on Obamacare. One breast cancer survivor told NBC News she feels caught in the middle of a political fight. NBC News' Ryan Nobles reports. Sherrone Moore has been detained by police after he was fired by the University of Michigan for cause. University officials said he was fired after an investigation found he had an "improper relationship with a staff member." NBC News' Shaquille Brewster reports. Six people were injured and multiple structures damaged after an explosion in Hayward, California. Doorcam video captured the moment the blast happened. NBC News' Steve Patterson has the story.In a recent email to parents and surrogates, Surro Connections wrote it was abruptly shutting down because of "financial and operation difficulties". Now, parents say they are unable to access tens of thousands of dollars they sent the company. NBC News' Liz Kreutz reports. Authorities in Australia have released their report on an incident involving a skydiver whose parachute inadvertently opened as he was about to jump. The video shows the unidentified man quickly cutting the cords to his back-up parachute to get safely to the ground. NBC News' George Solis has the story. As Rehema Ellis embarks on her next adventure, Nightly News celebrates a beloved member of the NBC family. Ellis has covered countless stories over the years and reported around the world. NBC News' Tom Llamas shares her story.
